      "writtenOn": "2017-02-14T02:30:21Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Yeah this is for case 5, when the guest just finished VertexAttribPointerData but does not yet get to glDrawElements_enc. In such situation GLESpointer needs to know the buffer size. And (the bad boy is) the existing GLESpointer.getSize() does not mean the buffer size. It actually means the number of channels. (Yeah horrible naming in GL spec)\n\nSo we don\u0027t actually have a buffer size in GLESpointer. The purpose of this function is to tell GLESpointer the buffer size so that we can correctly snapshot the buffer.",
